 we have
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{eqnarray*}
d_{ij} & = & \sum_{s=1}^{l}\left(\sum_{t=1}^{m}a_{it}b_{ts}\right)c_{sj}\\
 & = & \sum_{s=1}^{l}\sum_{t=1}^{m}\left(a_{it}b_{ts}\right)c_{sj}\\
 & = & \sum_{s=1}^{l}\sum_{t=1}^{m}a_{it}\left(b_{ts}c_{sj}\right)\\
 & = & \sum_{t=1}^{m}a_{it}\left(\sum_{s=1}^{l}b_{ts}c_{sj}\right)\\
 & = & e_{ij}
\end{eqnarray*}

\end_inset

for 
\begin_inset Formula $1\le i\le n$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $1\le j\le k$
\end_inset

, hence 
\begin_inset Formula $A\star\left(B\star C\right)=\left(A\star B\right)\star C$
\end_inset

.
