\lambda x' & =\lambda\left(x+S\right)\\
 & =\lambda x+\lambda s
\end{align*}

\end_inset

so that 
\begin_inset Formula $\lambda x'+S=\lambda x+\lambda s+S=\lambda x+S$
\end_inset

, since 
\begin_inset Formula $\lambda s\in S$
\end_inset

.
