\begin_layout Standard
More generally, for any (left) right module 
\begin_inset Formula $M$
\end_inset

 over a ring 
\begin_inset Formula $R$
\end_inset

, one may define a (left) right basis for 
\begin_inset Formula $M$
\end_inset

 as a subset 
\begin_inset Formula $B$
\end_inset

 of 
\begin_inset Formula $M$
\end_inset

 such that 
\begin_inset Formula $B$
\end_inset

