\emph on
second dual
\emph default
 or 
\emph on
bidual
\emph default
 of 
\begin_inset Formula $V$
\end_inset

.
 There 
\emph on
is
\emph default
 a very simple canonical injection 
\begin_inset Formula $V\longrightarrow\Vstarstar$
\end_inset

, and it is an isomorphism if the dimension of 
\begin_inset Formula $V$
\end_inset

