\begin_inset Formula 
\[
D=\begin{pmatrix}\lambda_{1} &  & 0\\
 & \ddots\\
0 &  & \lambda_{n}
\end{pmatrix}\quad\text{and}\quad S=\begin{pmatrix}| &  & |\\
\v_{1} & \cdots & \v_{n}\\
| &  & |
\end{pmatrix}\,,
\]

\end_inset

i.e.
\begin_inset space \space{}
\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula $\v_{1},\dots,\v_{n}$
\end_inset

 are the columns of the matrix 
\begin_inset Formula $S$
\end_inset

, equation 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "e.d"

\end_inset

 can be written 
\begin_inset Formula $SD=AS$
\end_inset

, or 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\begin{pmatrix}| &  & |\\
\lambda_{1}\v_{1} & \cdots & \lambda_{n}\v_{n}\\
| &  & |
\end{pmatrix}=A\,\begin{pmatrix}| &  & |\\
\v_{1} & \cdots & \v_{n}\\
| &  & |
\end{pmatrix}\,.
\]

\end_inset

If we separate this matrix equation 
\begin_inset Formula $n$
\end_inset

